{{!-- this template will render a form with fields for a transaction, it will dress the form with data from the {{user}} that is available. It will need client side javascript to event handle the form submit by taking the form field data, validating it, then sending it in a PUT request to "/profile/balance". It will handle the usual responses, code 200 - all good, 400 user did something bad, 500 server broke --}}


<h1>Update Balance</h1>

<p>User's balance: {{user.balance}}</p>


<form>
    <div class="form update-balance-form">
        <label for="current-balance">Current Balance</label>
        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="current-balance" aria-describedby="currentBalance" placeholder="{{user.balance}}">
    </div>
    <div>
        <button id="update-btn" type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Update</button>
        <button id="cancel-btn" type="submit" class="btn-primary">Cancel</button>
    </div>
</form>

<script src="/js/update-balance.js"></script>